{"abstract":[{"text":"Take advantage of custom decoding and encoding logic for the shared file storage persistence","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"strategy, as well as beta support for Swift’s native Testing framework.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.12","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","title":"Migrating to 1.12"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. This version of the library introduced 1 new"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"API, as well as beta support for Swift Testing."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Important","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Before following this migration guide be sure you have fully migrated to the newest","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tools of version 1.11. See ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides","type":"reference"},{"text":" for more information.","type":"text"}]}],"style":"important"},{"text":"Custom file storage coding","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Custom-file-storage-coding"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Version 1.10 of the Composable Architecture introduced a powerful tool for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"sharing state","type":"text"}],"overridingTitle":"sharing state","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" amongst your features, and included several built-in persistence"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"strategies, including file storage. This strategy, however, was not very flexible, and only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"supported the default JSON encoding and decoding offered by Swift."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In this version, you can now define custom encoding and decoding logic using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage(_:decode:encode:)"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Swift Testing","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Swift-Testing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 16 and Swift 6 come with a powerful new native testing framework. Existing test targets using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"XCTest can even incrementally adopt the framework and define new tests with Testing. Existing XCTest"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"test "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"helpers","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", however, are not compatible with the new framework, and so test tools like the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Composable Architecture’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TestStore"},{"type":"text","text":" did not work with it out of the box."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That changes with this version, which seamlessly supports XCTest "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"and","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Swift’s Testing framework."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can now create a test store in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Test"},{"type":"text","text":" and failures will be reported accordingly."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\